      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "orderedList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Preheat your oven to 425 degrees Fahrenheit. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. In a medium-sized frying pan over medium-high heat, bring the pomegranate molasses, maple syrup, butter, vanilla, rosemary, salt, and pepper to a boil. Continue to boil for 4 minutes then remove the pan from the heat and let it cool. Once it's cool to the touch, it should have the consistency of molasses.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Lay the salmon on the baking sheet and spread the thick pomegranate sauce on top, don't worry if it doesn't spread easily, it will once it's in the oven.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Bake the salmon for 8-9 minutes, just until the salmon reaches 140 degrees Fahrenheit. Spoon some of the sauce that has run onto the pan over the salmon.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "text": "Serve the salmon with sprigs of rosemary surrounding it and pomegranate seeds over the top.",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "troubleshooter",
        "attrs": {
          "intro": "A few of the more common issues, and what tends to fix them.",
          "items": [
            {
              "fix": "Salt a pinch at a time, tasting. A squeeze of lemon or splash of vinegar at the end lifts most savoury dishes.",
              "cause": "Underseasoned or no acid.",
              "symptom": "The dish tastes flat"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Pull off the heat a minute or two before you think it's done. Plate straight away, or transfer to a warmed serving dish.",
              "cause": "Carryover cooking, food keeps cooking on the hot pan after the heat goes off.",
              "symptom": "It's overcooked by the time it reaches the table"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Drop the heat and give it longer. A probe thermometer is the only reliable check for meat.",
              "cause": "Heat too high, browned the outside before the middle warmed through.",
              "symptom": "It's undercooked in the middle"
            },
            {
              "fix": "Reheat covered with a splash of stock or water, on a low heat. Microwave on 60% power if using one, gentler than full blast.",
              "cause": "Reheated uncovered, or no liquid in the pan.",
              "symptom": "The leftovers were dry"
            }
          ],
          "heading": "If something goes wrong"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
